column3: Bought to be used with a Huawei M10, it works really well, flows well and is very precise beyond all expectations. Now I'll give you the pros and cons: Pros: - It can be attached wherever you want in the shower and it stays there for hours thanks to the attached suction cup - It has LEDs and two modes that switch from one color to another so it also creates the atmosphere - The speaker's battery lasts a very long time (I charged it once and this will be the fifth shower without having recharged it again) - It's waterproof! Conclusion: I'm having a great time with this case and if you don't want to spend a lot but have the quality of a very expensive case that is also waterproof, get it now! 5/5 stars! Highly recommended

We know that pulsed light (and laser which however cannot be done at home) is the future of hair removal but the prices are exorbitant... with this device it is possible to have EXCELLENT results even at home!

As far as sports features are concerned, I don't think you could wish for more, it allows you to track any parameter of physical activity and even counts the hours of sleep! You can even select which app can send notifications and you can control the music playing on Spotify. All this allows you to watch notifications select music without even having to touch your smartphone. I read that the Alexa voice assistant will also be added in the future which makes it an even more solid investment. Highly recommended!

column2: For iPad it is the best
column3: I tried to buy this HUB because I recently got an iPad and since I will use it a lot for work I need to connect different devices to it. There are 2 USB 3.0 ports that allow you to connect a USB stick, a mouse and a wireless keyboard at the same time (mouse and keyboard must have a common Bluetooth receiver as in my case) I can simultaneously connect the iPad to the TV (in my case it served on several occasions to illustrate photo albums to various clients) and I can download the photos and videos I take directly onto the iPad thanks to the SD and MicroSD ports. A perhaps little-recognized gem that many other HUBs don't have is the Ethernet port which allows you to connect the iPad to an even faster connection, saving connection battery by deactivating the WiFi antenna. Perhaps I won't use this function much personally thanks to the iPad's lightning-fast WiFi, but if like me you have to deal with the most disparate cases in studios and clients' homes, it is a potential lifeline that can make the difference. I also connected it to the Switch Lite, thus having access to a completely different level of gaming experience... In fact, I can connect a Joypad and recharge the console while playing by placing the Switch on a support. Unfortunately, no, it is not possible to connect it to the TV with HDMI. The Switch Lite does not have coding for video transmission like the basic version but the usability of the console is significantly improved. The only flaw found is the speed of reading the USB 2.0 stick. The iPad struggles a lot to read photo files but we are talking about large sizes (each photo weighs 15MB on average). I cannot know with extreme certainty what the cause is, the Hub or the pen drive which, being a 2.0, has a much slower transfer speed. Maybe with a 3.0 I wouldn't have had this problem. The dimensions are not small but given the many functions it is presumed to be used on a table or in any case on office supports. However, the weight is not excessive and does not strain the USB-C inputs.

Let's start with the delivery arrived on time. The box is made of cardboard with illustrations. Inside there is the deterrent, the charging cable and the mounting accessories. The rechargeable batteries are already mounted. The owl shape is very cute, time will tell if the pigeons will be afraid of it. There are two eyes with white and red flashing alarm LEDs and a piezo tweeter for ultrasound. It can be fixed with the hook or with the aluminum support divided into two pieces. The two potentiometers should be used, one to select the frequency based on the animals to be removed, the second to adjust the volume. Some frequencies are also audible to humans. Robust construction. The motion sensor lights up when charging red and turns green. Good product.

column2: Precise and reliable, I recommend it

"I had been thinking about buying a projector for a long time but the excessively high prices of the most popular brands scared me and while doing some research I came across this projector. I appreciated the ventilation system is not too invasive during projection."

column2: Very useful charging station for my home office
column3: I really appreciated the USB charging station. Every day I find myself having to charge and power various electronic devices and this object has made my life easier. The hub I chose has 2 Type C ports and 2 Type A ports. All 4 inputs support fast charge charging my smartphone and even my laptop. Very minimal and elegant object, well assembled with quality glossy plastic. Super recommended, a must have in every home!

The product, as shown in the photo, arrived intact, working and complete, also with instructions in Italian. Packaging: Careful and sturdy, the machine like all the other components does not move during transport, even the guarantee seal is present (certifies that no one has opened it). The pack beyond the machine contains a scrub brush for the face/neck area of the right softness, neither too hard to be annoying nor too soft to have to be thrown away after the first use. (look at the photos to understand what it contains and how it gets there) Functionality: Very easy to use (in case of problems there are instructions in Italian) it has a tilting head that allows you to cut all the hair even while sitting in the tub the head is very easy it needs to be washed, it is also waterproof so there are no problems. It is very light and easy to transport. If you put it in your suitcase, it takes up less than 20cm. Having USB charging you can use the phone adapter, still saving space. Battery Life: The charging phase is signaled through a flashing of the LED when the charge has reached 100% the LED remains fixed. To recharge the first time it took about 2 hours, used it for 45 minutes and put it away, still working. TOP battery After 4 days of use: Satisfied with the purchase I would recommend it!

Let me start by saying that at home, given that I am in an area where even my neighbors who have an antenna on the roof sometimes lose the signal, I have installed a satellite dish to watch satellite TV with TivuSat. I put a TV under my roof in which I connected the Tim vision to watch Tim/netflix content etc. I wanted to try this antenna to see if it was possible to see DVB TV channels. Installation is super quick, you just have to screw the stem to the base and connect the cable to the TV either directly if it's a screw or with the adapter supplied together with the USB plug to the TV. When I connected it as you can see from the photo placed on the bin after I scanned it I was surprised. You can see DVB channels and even some in HD. For now I use it by placing it on the bin or on the table and so far it hasn't given me any major problems. Some channels can't be seen but the main ones can. Considering the low support I'm sure that if I had been on a raised floor everyone would be seen. However, overall I can be satisfied considering the price is not exaggerated. Do I recommend it? Certainly yes for those like me who don't have the possibility of bringing a TV cable or installing a high-cost antenna.

Definitely the best robot vacuum cleaner I've ever purchased. Let me start by saying that I am a fan of electronic and smart accessories and this is the 3 robot vacuum cleaners that I buy every time trying to find something better. I was very very happy, the only flaw of my old robots was having to continually empty the dust box so as not to clog up the robot and this compromised many of the automatic cleanings organized during the week. Thanks to its HUGE charging station, this robot has the ability to suck dust directly from the robot thanks to the special autonomous vacuum cleaner and fills the bag like a traditional old school vacuum cleaner. Obviously it allows you to empty the dirt much more sporadically than the collection boxes found inside the robots themselves. The assortment of accessories and spare parts supplied is also excellent (ps. there are also many spare bags). The smart interface of the robot is very advanced. Alexa App etc.. you can clearly see that it is top of the range type. Finally, I would like to talk about its cleaning characteristics. The robot is very silent but has excellent suction power. It is also really intelligent and able to understand when it is on carpets or in areas of the house that are forbidden to it. Definitely the best cleaning robot ever purchased. I recommend spending a little more and buying these products rather than perhaps having to change them after less than a year because they are unsatisfactory.

this tool itself is well designed. the possibility of quickly replacing the blades is an ingenious and useful thing. unfortunately I have to say that as soon as the small cutter was mounted on the round neck drill the set screw lost its hold probably due to the poor quality (antimony?) and the blade it was running in circles. However, I solved the problem by putting an old Allen screw that I had among the scrap in storage after having worn out and thinned the part of the bottom of the drill bit (which serves to center the hole) where the set screw meets the tip. in this way the screw threads deeper and is able to block the tip well. the fact remains that I had to adapt and remedy a structural defect

I don't know if this could penalize its duration or quality. I would buy them again but always as high beams and not as low beams, I'm afraid they won't last too long.

the audio is very good as is the noise isolation, unfortunately during a telephone call the interlocutor has low volume problems. as happens with this type of earphones, the microphones are always not very sensitive... never mind...
